<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.1-2_0001a" />

<fw type="letterhead">
JOHN G. NEIHARDT
<lb/>
5835 VINE STREET
<lb/>
LINCOLN, NEBR. 68505
</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>Jan. 1, '70</dateline>

<salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
</opener>
<p>Bruce Nicoll has just sent me a copy of the <hi rend="double underline">Danish</hi> edition of <hi rend="underline">Black Elk Speaks</hi>! I had not even heard that the Danes wanted it. Now there are <hi rend="double underline">six</hi> foreign language editions of the book! And there will be more and more.</p>

<p>Fred Lee writes giving the latest quotations on 

<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.1-2_0001b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>   <fw type="curatorial"><del/></fw>

The Indian Wars (boxed) $35 The Collected Poems $45 Isn't this bully?! The prices of all my out of print books are going up and up, which signifies a prevalent belief among collectors that I will grow in value &#8212; <unclear>survive</unclear> our time.</p>   

<p>John Madden has offered the fine portrait done by <choice><sic>Szas</sic><corr>Szasz</corr></choice> to the Neihardt Foundation in Bancroft.</p>

<fw type="curatorial">1</fw>
<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.1-2_0002a"/>
<fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>

<p>I am eager to get started on negotiations with Nicoll. Will <hi rend="underline">you</hi> want to contact <del>him</del> him before Random &amp; Holt?</p>

<p>We need to hurry with the next steps. We cannot afford to waste any time now.</p>

<p>I hope you are not unpleasantly surprised at the <hi rend="double underline">deceivingly long list</hi> of corrections indicated. It's <hi rend="underline">not</hi> <del>really</del>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.61.1-2_0002b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>

<del>really formidable</del>
really formidable at all, as you'll see when you get at it.</p>
<closer>
<salute>Love ever and ever &#8212;</salute>

<signed>John N.</signed>
<signed>Gaki</signed>
</closer>

<note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
